<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/48242853-andrea-martin"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1586663462i/48242853._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/48242853-andrea-martin">Andrea Martin</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I don&apos;t think that any book is able to change your belief in anything that drastically. However, I do think that anything that makes you doubt should <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I don't think that any book is able to change your belief in anything that drastically. However, I do think that anything that makes you doubt should be faced to consolidate a stronger base and avoid having our schemes blown away easily. Anyone interested in the field of religion knows how many struggles someone must constantly face, so with this book it could be your turn now. Goodluck!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
