  <span id="freeText6537078962754599081" style="display:none">Back in the good old days where religion was the only neurotic illusion masses suffered from, I guess. <br /><br />I suggest reading <i>Totem and Taboo</i> before diving into this one in order to understand the train of thought behind how religious beliefs originated from toteism, which has, in turn, the father complex in its core. <br /><br />Are his arguments demolishing religious belief? No, but they're doing a hell of a good job explaining the reasons behind it as well as the way they have allowed civilizations to progress so far and avoid self-destruction. <br /><br />Well, judging from current events, even that last bit is debatable. </span>
