<span id="freeTextContainer722297294630503272">Freud gets a lot of crap nowadays for the obsession with Oedipal type thoughts but he remains a good read. This is a short little book on religious illusions that was pretty thoughtful and optimistic. I liked it, but if I&apos;m delusional in thinking it was good, I will accept the counter arguments and hopefully be less neurotic afterwards.</span>
  <span id="freeText722297294630503272" style="display:none">Freud gets a lot of crap nowadays for the obsession with Oedipal type thoughts but he remains a good read. This is a short little book on religious illusions that was pretty thoughtful and optimistic. I liked it, but if I'm delusional in thinking it was good, I will accept the counter arguments and hopefully be less neurotic afterwards.</span>
