<div id="review_3023564690" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3023564690" />
    <a title="Fanie Oosthuysen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66086616-fanie-oosthuysen"><img alt="Fanie Oosthuysen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1489930809p2/66086616.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3023564690?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fanie Oosthuysen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fanie Oosthuysen" href="/user/show/66086616-fanie-oosthuysen">Fanie Oosthuysen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11761603-the-future-of-an-illusion">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3023564690" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer682353704602656744">Dare I psychoanalyze the father of Psychoanalytics. This book, some other books by Freud like Civilization and it&apos;s Discontents and some later analysis by Carl Jung is a nice way to deep research Freuds own familial relationship problems and troubles growing up, especially his relationship with his own father expressed in a psychological way as intellectual distaste for religion. Religion was thus a blind spot for him and this blind spot grew as he aged, and unlike Carl Jung who had a better und</span>
  <span id="freeText682353704602656744" style="display:none">Dare I psychoanalyze the father of Psychoanalytics. This book, some other books by Freud like Civilization and it's Discontents and some later analysis by Carl Jung is a nice way to deep research Freuds own familial relationship problems and troubles growing up, especially his relationship with his own father expressed in a psychological way as intellectual distaste for religion. Religion was thus a blind spot for him and this blind spot grew as he aged, and unlike Carl Jung who had a better understanding of humanities' relationship to religion and more importantly religions' relationship to humanity, Freud definitely missed it. The criticisms of his views published in this very book, he overlooks, and misses the point of those arguments fully. This is obvious to me in his responses to them and with that, he missed the opportunity to identify, reflect-on and solve his own psychological barriers holding onto the idiology of the enlightenment as a replacement to religion so hard-headedly that he may have missed the opportunity for a more emotionally and dare I say spiritually fulfilled life. That being said what this man and his mentees did for our ability to study human thought and it's effects was miraculous.</span>
  <a data-text-id="682353704602656744" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

